parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Warped brake rotors can cause the vehicle to vibrate or pull to one side when braking, leading to reduced stopping power and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Vehicle vibrates or pulls to one side when braking
loud grinding or screeching noise when braking
brake pedal pulsates or feels spongy
uneven brake rotor wear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failed brake pads can cause the vehicle to take longer to stop, leading to increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Squealing or grinding noise when braking
brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pads excessively worn
vehicle takes longer to stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the master cylinder can cause a loss of brake fluid, leading to reduced stopping power and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Brake fluid leak
brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pedal drops to the floor
vehicle takes longer to stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty suspension system sensor can cause the suspension light to malfunction, leading to inaccurate warnings and potential safety risks, as well as unnecessary repairs and financial burdens on the vehicle owner.
symptoms: The suspension light flashes or remains illuminated on the dashboard
despite the absence of any actual suspension issues
and may be accompanied by inaccurate warnings or error messages.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Inaccurate Diagnostic and Repair by Dealership
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Inaccurate diagnostic and repair by the dealership can lead to unnecessary repairs, financial burdens, and continued safety risks, as well as erosion of trust in the dealership and the vehicle manufacturer.
symptoms: The dealership provides incorrect diagnoses or estimates for repairs
performs unnecessary repairs
or fails to resolve the issue
leading to repeated visits and financial losses for the vehicle owner.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunctioning IAC valve can cause the engine to stall or die without warning, leading to a loss of control and increased risk of accidents, especially in warmer weather conditions.
symptoms: Erratic idle
idle revving and dropping
idle dipping often with engine dying
idle hanging high above 2
000 RPM
engine dying or stalling for no reason with no trouble codes. These symptoms often occur only in warmer weather
typically starting in the spring and subsiding in the fall with cooler weather.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the idle control system can cause the engine to stall or nearly stall, leading to a loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents, especially when driving in heavy traffic or navigating steep inclines.
symptoms: The engine idle speed drops suddenly
the engine RPM fluctuates erratically
the engine RPM surges to high levels (e.g.
2000 RPM) and remains there for an extended period (e.g.
30 seconds)
the engine RPM slowly returns to normal after the surge.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbags to deploy in the event of a crash can increase the risk of serious injury or fatality to occupants.
symptoms: Airbags do not deploy in a crash
warning lights or indicators on the dashboard
audible warnings or chimes
seatbelt pretensioners do not tighten.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Inconsistent or Erratic Airbag Warning Lights
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Inconsistent or erratic airbag warning lights can lead to confusion or complacency among drivers, potentially increasing the risk of injury or fatality in the event of a crash.
symptoms: Airbag warning lights illuminate intermittently
airbag warning lights remain illuminated constantly
airbag warning lights fail to illuminate
audible warnings or chimes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A malfunctioning crash sensor can prevent airbags from deploying in the event of a crash, increasing the risk of serious injury or fatality to occupants.
symptoms: Airbags do not deploy in a crash
crash sensors damaged or faulty
warning lights or indicators on the dashboard
audible warnings or chimes.
